"The sudden onset and depth of the crisis in the fall of 2008 mirrored the fears in Congress today.
In September 2008, Congress approved the then-record-breaking $700 billion Troubled Asset Relief Program, or TARP, with a bipartisan vote.
Democrats retained control of Congress that Novemeber and immediately got to work on a massive stimulus with newly elected President Obama.
